      "date": "2012-03-21 10:08:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nsorry, I didn't go into details.. we discussed in Beijing that this functionality (lfsck, not scrubber, btw) should not rely on mdd, but can run under mdd for a while. so that at some point we should be able to run in on OSS or on LUT. literally this mean no structure like mdd_device or mdd_object should be used. only dt_* ones.",
