      "date": "2012-03-27 02:08:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n> sorry, I didn't go into details.. we discussed in Beijing that this functionality (lfsck, not scrubber, btw) should not rely on mdd, but can run under mdd for a while. so that at some point we should be able to run in on OSS or on LUT. literally this mean no structure like mdd_device or mdd_object should be used. only dt_* ones.\n\nIn the new patch, the MDD layer scrub engine will use dt_* based elements, will not depends on MDD implementation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
