          {
            "commit": "861cfca844dbc5613b520c9b1d9fa39ef4f8221a",
            "subject": "LU-957 scrub: osd-ldiskfs inode iterator"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-04-08 06:42:22.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-04-08 06:47:46.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 scrub: LFSCK main engine",
        "message": "LU-957 scrub: LFSCK main engine\n\nImplement the main engine for Lustre online fsck.\nThe kernel thread \"md_scrub\" scans the system by\nDT iteration APIs, and drives registered scrub\ncomponents to check/repair Lustre system.\n\nIt is the main controller of the whole Lustre fsck,\nand controls the LFSCK speed.\n\nNormally, if the OSD layer iteration FID cache is full,\nthen OSD layer OI scrub will wait until some slots are\navailable (released by the \"md_scrub\" iteration). So OI\nscrub speed is controlled by the \"md_scrub\" also.\n\nFor urgent mode, like MDT is restored from file-level\nbackup, the OI files are invalided. Under such case,\nwe need to rebuild the OI files ASAP, then low layer\nOI scrub will ignore the main engine iteration, and\nif the cache is full, it will go without waiting.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic080b4992f7d27d627bb7fb648bb75d280c94008\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
